What's next?

After confirming your account, you can begin to test the DPC API and build your solution in sandbox using synthetic data. For more information, review our documentation (https://dpc.cms.gov/docs) and Github page (https://github.com/CMSgov/dpc-app/blob/master/src/main/resources/README.md). 

When you are ready to demonstrate your DPC solution with our team and get access to production data, you may apply to join the production pilot onboarding queue (https://airtable.com/shr3m3BL3IWY5hYnm). For more information, visit our About the Pilot page (https://dpc.cms.gov/pilot).

Comments? Questions?

If you have any questions or would like to share feedback, please reach out through our Google Group (https://groups.google.com/g/dpc-api). If you require immediate assistance with registration or logging in, please email us directly at DPCINFO@cms.hhs.gov. 

We look forward to hearing about your experiences and learning about your innovative ways to serve Medicare beneficiaries.

